A lone explorer in vintage safari attire stands at the edge of a dense, overgrown jungle made entirely of towering stacked paper documents and scrolls, their pages yellowed and weathered. The documents form twisted vines, canopy layers, and tangled undergrowth. Ancient-looking calendar grids and date wheels are carved into massive stone monuments scattered throughout, partially consumed by the paper vegetation. Shafts of warm golden light pierce through gaps in the document canopy. The explorer holds an old compass and worn leather satchel, peering into the mysterious depths ahead. Muted sepia and cream tones dominate with occasional touches of faded ink blue and aged parchment gold. Vintage illustration style reminiscent of 1920s adventure book covers, with crosshatching textures and slightly worn edges.
